  "chunk_index": 12,
  "summary": "David Hunter enters Room 5 at the Stagg to meet a man identifying himself as Inok Jacobson, though the man also uses the aliases Enock Yatton or Judd. David observes that the man appears worn-out and elusive. During their meeting over whiskey, the man reveals that he knew David’s sister Rosaline’s first husband, Robert André, very well.\n\nThe man claims that André did not die in Africa as believed, but instead faked his death to manipulate local natives and reappear under a new name. He implies that if André were to reappear, it would reveal that Rosaline’s current marriage to Gordon Claude is bigamous, which would potentially invalidate her inheritance and Gordon Claude's prenuptial agreement. The man asserts that André is alive but in poor health and requires expensive medical treatment.\n\nWhen David accuses the man of extortion, the man threatens to go public with this information to the Claude family. To protect his sister and her status, David agrees to pay. After the man initially demands two million, David refuses, noting that Rosaline cannot touch her principal investment. The man lowers his demand to one million. David agrees to the payment on the condition that it be made in cash, instructing the man to bring the money to the Stagg on Tuesday night at nine o'clock. David leaves the room in a state of intense anger.",
